{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17585255","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17585255"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:07:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:07:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14943"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14943","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14943"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.25,0.11,0.06,0.47,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7631"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66430"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7631","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7631"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14943"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51881"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5440"},{"type":"tags","id":"7882"},{"type":"tags","id":"8095"},{"type":"tags","id":"9982"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18666"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18667"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66430","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66430"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EViruses have evolved various mechanisms to evade host immune responses. Some viruses produce proteins that closely resemble host immune molecules to manipulate the immune system.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following cytokines does Epstein-Barr virus mimic to suppress cell-mediated immunity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["IL-2","IL-3","IL-7","IL-10","IL-13"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EEpstein-Barr virus\u003C/em\u003E produces a viral homologue of \u003Cstrong\u003EIL-10\u003C/strong\u003E (vIL-10) that helps the virus evade immune detection. This viral protein suppresses protective cell-mediated immune responses while promoting B cell proliferation, where the virus preferentially replicates.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIL-2\u003C/strong\u003E promotes T cell proliferation and differentiation, enhancing rather than suppressing cell-mediated immunity\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIL-3\u003C/strong\u003E primarily acts as a growth factor for early hematopoietic progenitors\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIL-7\u003C/strong\u003E is essential for T and B cell development but does not specifically modulate immune responses\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIL-13\u003C/strong\u003E is involved in allergic responses and does not have broad immunosuppressive effects\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis viral mimicry of IL-10 represents a sophisticated immune evasion strategy that helps establish persistent infection by creating an environment favorable for viral replication.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Epstein-Barr virus produces a viral IL-10 homologue (vIL-10) that suppresses cell-mediated immunity and promotes B cell proliferation.","Viral immune evasion strategies often involve mimicking host cytokines to modulate the immune response.","IL-10 is an immunoregulatory cytokine that suppresses T cell responses while promoting B cell function."],"references":["Sastry, A. S., \u0026 Bhat, S. (2018). Essentials of medical microbiology. JP Medical Ltd","Hoover K, Higginbotham K. Epstein-Barr Virus. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK559285/","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51881"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14943"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51881","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51881"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-30T09:01:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-30T09:03:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7631"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66430"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4936","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4936"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udee1\ufe0f","name":"Immune System","synon